  "text": "Previous studies of biocompatible PDFs were associated with decreased interleukin-6 synthesis and vascular endothelial growth factor secretion. These data suggest that the biocompatible PDFs are associated with reduced intraperitoneal inflammation and reduced potential for angiogenesis (36, [CITATION_1] . The higher levels of CRP in the C-PDF group at all follow-up visits may reflect an increase in chronic inflammation among PD patients treated with conventional PDFs compared to those treated with the novel PDFs in this study.",
